## Troubleshooting — Common Issues and Fixes

### Dolt Issues

**"database is read only"**
The dolt clone was created without write permissions. Re-clone:
```bash
rm -rf /tmp/mesh-sync-clone
GT_ROOT=$GT_ROOT bash .gt-mesh/scripts/mesh-sync.sh
```

**"permission denied" on dolt clone**
Dolt credentials not configured or expired:
```bash
dolt creds ls          # Check active credential
dolt creds use <id>    # Switch to valid credential
```

**"merge conflict" on dolt pull**
Multiple agents wrote to the same table simultaneously:
```bash
cd /tmp/mesh-sync-clone
dolt conflicts resolve --ours .
dolt add . && dolt commit -m "resolve merge conflict"
dolt push
```

### Git Issues

**"push rejected" (non-fast-forward)**
Someone else pushed while you were working:
```bash
git pull --rebase && git push
```

**Worker branch has no commits**
Worker died before committing. Check for uncommitted files:
```bash
git status --short
git ls-files --others --exclude-standard
```
Rescue files manually, commit from coordinator workspace.

### Mesh Issues

**Messages not delivering**
Check sync is running:
```bash
GT_ROOT=$GT_ROOT bash .gt-mesh/scripts/mesh-sync.sh
```

**Peer shows stale last_seen**
The peer's sync daemon may have stopped. Nudge them or check their session.

### Bead Issues

**"unknown flag" errors with bd/gt commands**
Check the command syntax — flags may have changed between versions.
